Operatives of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, EFCC, Maiduguri Zonal Command, have arraigned one Isyaku Ibrahim on a one-count amended charge of criminal misappropriation to the tune of N12 million. According to a statement issued via its verified Twitter handle on Wednesday, the accused was arraigned before Justice Umaru Fadawu of the Borno State High Court. Ibrahim was charged with criminally misappropriating properties belonging to one late Muhammad Ishiyaku for his personal use, to the detriment of the deceasedâ€™s family. The properties mentioned in the charge include three houses, two fenced lands, one of which has seven shops, two bread factories, one open land, two tanker trucks, and one big installed generator, all valued at N12 million. The defendant has been remanded and the case adjourned till July 12.